Lung Gar Buddhist Academy is home to 40,000 monks and nuns to study Tibetan Buddhism . 
  The settlement of Sertar is the world's largest Buddhist settlement and is located in the Larung Gar Valley in China . 
  Monks and nuns are housed in red wooden huts and separated by age and sex  . 
  The settlement has grown from a handful of disciples in the 1980s to become the largest in the world . 
 